Product Description▼▲
How do we find faith in our materialistic culture? Is it possible to believe in Christ? Brian Draper approaches the subject in an imaginative, poetic way, drawing on images from contemporary culture to help present the case for Christianity. Section one (The Way) examines who Jesus was, the path we should choose, and the radical challenge of following Jesus. Section two (The Truth) looks at our broken world, how to find real peace, and authenticity. Section three (The Life) answers questions such as "Must I go to church to be a Christian?" and "How do I make the most of my life?"

