Publisher's Description▼▲
How do we find faith today in our materialistic culture? Is it possible to believe in Christ? Brian Draper approaches the subject in an imaginative, poetic way, drawing on images from contemporary culture to help present the case for Christianity.Section One: THE WAY• Who was Jesus?• What path should I choose?• The radical challenge of following JesusSection Two: THE TRUTH• How come everything is so screwed up?• What do I have to do to get some peace round here?• Authenticity and the search for the realSection Three: THE LIFE • How do I make the most of my life?


Author Bio▼▲
Brian Draper is a lecturer in contemporary culture at the London Institute for Contemporary Christianity. He was formerly editor of ThirdWay magazine. He has a monthly column on culture in the Christian Herald and also writes for the Church Times. Recently, he has begun writing and presenting for BBC Radio 4's 'Thought for the Day' on the Today program. He has also written extensively for U2.com and for Amazon.


